# GBVIMS+ Mobile

In developed and stable settings it is challenging to obtain reliable data on gender-based violence. Humanitarian contexts where institutions, infrastructure, and human resources may be weakened or compromised pose further challenges. Ethical and safety issues around data collection, management and sharing are paramount to ensuring survivor safety and recovery. In some settings, using traditional paper-based information management systems invites opportunities for breaches of confidentiality, theft of sensitive data, and erodes opportunities for analysis to improve programming.  This includes settings that may be prone to casual intrusion by soldiers, rebels or community members and settings where we do not have a static office and services are provided in mobile or changing settings.​

The GBVIMS+ mobile application was developed to respond to these type of settings, allowing for caseworkers and other frontline staff to have a safer way to track incidents and individual survivors \(women and girls\) progress as they go through the case management process following an act of gender-based violence.​

It’s great that we have the mobile for data entry, a couple of reminders though – this is solely for the purpose of data entry, not referrals or transfers or supervision or flagging. This has one purpose. This doesn’t have the total functionality of the web version, so it’s best to use the two in tandem.

### Log In

  ![](data:image/png;base64,%)

1. Enter the username​
2. Enter the password​
3. Enter the web URL

Note: multiple users can use the same device.

### Main Menu: Cases

  ![](data:image/png;base64,%)

After logging in, the application will redirect to the main menu.​

1.Select Case on main menu, then the case list will be displayed.​

  ![](data:image/png;base64,%)

2. Click on the **"+"** icon on the bottom right of the page to open the short case form. Then the short form of case creation page will be displayed. The short form allows users to enter a case record with basic information only. ​

  ![](data:image/png;base64,%)

3. Enter the information for the case.​

  ![](data:image/png;base64,%)

4. You can save the information by clicking on save in the upper right hand corner.​

  ![](data:image/png;base64,%)

5. When selecting information from a long list, a text field will be available to search for specific values. \(On some devices, the keyboard will automatically show up, if it’s not needed, please click on “Back” button on device to hide the keyboard.\)​

  ![](data:image/jpg;base64,%)

6. To enter more information than the short form.  Click on ‘Show more details’

  ![](data:image/png;base64,%)

### Viewing an Existing Case

In the list view, click on any case to review the details.​

  ![](data:image/png;base64,%)

### Adding an Incident

1. On case view page, click add incident icon can create an incident related to this case. \(note : one case can add more than one related incident\)​

  ![](data:image/png;base64,%)  ![](data:image/png;base64,%)

2. Click on the pencil icon to enter information​

3. Then save.​

4. Once saved, you can find a link to the incidents in the case section under action plan.

**NOTE:** Always complete the status of the incidents and cases as ‘**open**’ if you want to be able to see these records on your platform.

  ![](data:image/jpg;base64,%)

### Edit a Case or Incident

On the full form of any case or incident record, click on the pencil icon on bottom right.

  ![](data:image/png;base64,%)

### Search for Cases or Incidents

1. On the list view, click on the magnifying glass icon to navigate to search.​
2. Enter any keywords to search specific cases.

  ![](data:image/png;base64,%)  ![](data:image/png;base64,%)

### Sort Cases

On the list view, click on the order column on the top of the page to sort cases.

  ![](data:image/png;base64,%)

### Synchronization

![](.gitbook/assets/image%20%286%29.png)

1. Select Synchronization on main menu, then the Synchronization page will be displayed.​

  ![](data:image/png;base64,%)    

2. Click on the synchronization button, and the sync information will appear.​

![](data:image/jpg;base64,%)

3. Clicking on the sync button, a popup will be displayed showing the progress.​

  ![](data:image/jpg;base64,%)  ![](data:image/jpg;base64,%)  ![](data:image/jpg;base64,%)

\* After records in mobile app are synced to web app, mobile app will automatically pull records which are marked for mobile.

### How to see a Case or Incident from the web app on a mobile

If the user begins data entry on the mobile device, they can sync that data to the web server.​

Once synced to the web server, the user can continue data entry on the web app.​

Data will only update on the mobile, if the user selected ‘Mark for Mobile.’  Users will have to remember to mark for mobile on the web if they want the record to sync back to the mobile.​

![](.gitbook/assets/image%20%287%29.png)

If the user starts the data entry on a computer/laptop on the web app, then ‘Mark for Mobile,’ the user can finish data entry on the mobile device, and sync it back to the web server when they’re finished.

### ​Deleting a Case

1.On the list page, click on the trash icon in the upper right hand corner.​

  ![](data:image/png;base64,%)

2. Then select the cases to delete​

  ![](data:image/png;base64,%)

3. Select delete. \*Not synced record are greyed out and can’t be selected.​

  ![](data:image/png;base64,%)

4. After pressing delete, there will be a confirmation message.  To confirm, press ‘Yes.’

### Delete the Application

In the case of an emergency, or casual intrusion, the application can be deleted to protect survivor confidentiality.  There are several options for deleting the application.​

**Option 1​**

1. Press and Hold the app icon \(either on desktop or application list\), until a trash icon is displayed on the screen.​
2. Then drag app icon to the trash icon.​
3. Confirm app deletion.

**Option 2​**

1. Go to Settings​
2. Go to Apps/Applications.​
3. Select the mobile app icon \(RapidReg\)​
4. Then click on uninstall button.​
5. Then confirm and delete the app.
